Henrikh Mkhitaryan had a difficult time at Arsenal but the midfielder looks like he is getting back to his best at Roma this season. The 31-year-old joined the Gunners from Manchester United two years ago in a swap deal that saw Alexis Sanchez go the other way. But Mkhitaryan failed to impress Unai Emery and was sent on a season long loan to Roma after scoring nine goals in 59 appearances for Arsenal. Watch the video here. The post Watch: Arsenal loanee Henrikh Mkhitaryan gets goal & assist appeared first on Football365. Source: Football 365